      <chapter>
        <title>The Turning Point of Barilla</title>
        <paragraph>Barilla began its Smart Working program in 2013, allowing some of its employees to work at home the 13% of their total hours per month. Currently the program has been extended to 1200 employees, that can work 40% of their hours per month outside the workplace. Barilla aim to include all its employees to the program by 2020, letting them work any time they want outside the workplace.</paragraph>
      </chapter>
